.TH H5I 1 "2026-03-28" "h5i 0.1.0" "h5i Manual"
.
.SH NAME
h5i \- Advanced Git sidecar for the AI era
.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B h5i
.I COMMAND
.RI [ OPTIONS ]
.RI [ ARGUMENTS ]
.
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B h5i
(\"high-five\") extends Git with five semantic dimensions:
.PP
.RS 4
.IP \(bu 2
.B Temporal
\(em standard Git history
.IP \(bu 2
.B Structural
\(em AST-level snapshots and diffs
.IP \(bu 2
.B Intentional
\(em AI provenance (model, agent, prompt, token count)
.IP \(bu 2
.B Empirical
\(em test metrics attached to every commit
.IP \(bu 2
.B Associative
\(em CRDT-based collaborative editing
.RE
.PP
All metadata is stored as a Git sidecar under
.I .git/.h5i/
and two custom refs
.RI ( refs/h5i/notes
and
.IR refs/h5i/memory ).
These refs are
.B not
pushed by a plain
.BR "git push" ;
use
.B h5i push
to share them.
.
.SH COMMANDS
.
.\" ─── init ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
.SS h5i init
Initialize the h5i sidecar in the current Git repository.
Creates
.I .git/.h5i/
with subdirectories
.BR ast/ ,
.BR crdt/ ,
.BR delta/ ,
.BR memory/ ,
and
.BR session_log/ .
.
.\" ─── commit ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
.SS h5i commit \-m \fIMESSAGE\fR [\fIOPTIONS\fR]
Commit staged changes with optional AI provenance, test metrics,
AST snapshot, and integrity audit.
.PP
.B Options
.RS 4
.TP
.BI \-m,\ \-\-message\  MESSAGE
Git commit message (required).
.TP
.BI \-\-prompt\  TEXT
The user prompt that triggered this commit.
Falls back to env
.B H5I_PROMPT
or
.I .git/.h5i/pending_context.json
(written by the Claude Code hook).
.TP
.BI \-\-model\  NAME
AI model name, e.g.\&
.IR claude\-sonnet\-4\-6 .
Falls back to env
.BR H5I_MODEL .
.TP
.BI \-\-agent\  ID
Agent identifier, e.g.\&
.IR claude\-code .
Falls back to env
.BR H5I_AGENT_ID .
.TP
.BI \-\-caused\-by\  OID
Commit OID that causally triggered this one.
Repeatable:
.BR "\-\-caused\-by abc123 \-\-caused\-by def456" .
Abbreviated OIDs are resolved at commit time.
.TP
.BI \-\-test\-results\  FILE
Path to a JSON test results file produced by any adapter.
Takes precedence over
.B \-\-tests
and env
.BR H5I_TEST_RESULTS .
Schema: see
.B TEST RESULTS SCHEMA
below.
.TP
.BI \-\-test\-cmd\  CMD
Shell command whose stdout is parsed as h5i test JSON.
Used when no
.B \-\-test\-results
file is provided.
.TP
.B \-\-tests
Scan staged source files for inline
.B // h5_i_test_start
/
.B // h5_i_test_end
markers.
.TP
.B \-\-ast
Capture an AST snapshot of staged files for semantic blame.
.TP
.B \-\-audit
Run all twelve integrity rules before committing.
Violations block the commit;
.B \-\-force
overrides warnings only.
.TP
.B \-\-force
Commit despite integrity
.I warnings
(violations still block).
.RE
.PP
.B Flag resolution order:
CLI flag \(rA environment variable \(rA pending context file.
.
.\" ─── log ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
.SS h5i log [\fIOPTIONS\fR]
Display the enriched 5D commit history annotated with AI metadata,
test results, and causal links.
.PP
.B Options
.RS 4
.TP
.BI \-l,\ \-\-limit\  N
Number of recent commits to display (default:
.BR 10 ).
.RE
.
.\" ─── blame ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
.SS h5i blame \fIFILE\fR [\fIOPTIONS\fR]
Show per-line (or per-node) authorship annotated with AI metadata
and test status.
Each line shows two status columns:
test status
.RB ( \(OK\ passing ,\ \(mu\ failing ,\ blank\ =\ no\ data )
and AI indicator
.RB ( \(** )
for AI-authored lines.
.PP
.B Options
.RS 4
.TP
.BI \-m,\ \-\-mode\  MODE
.BR line \ (default)\ or\  ast .
AST mode associates authorship with AST nodes rather than source lines.
.RE
.
.\" ─── diff ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
.SS h5i diff \fIFILE\fR [\fIOPTIONS\fR]
Show the AST-level structural diff for a file.
Supported languages include Python.
.PP
.B Options
.RS 4
.TP
.BI \-\-from\  OID
Compare from this commit (default: HEAD).
.TP
.BI \-\-to\  OID
Compare to this commit (default: working-tree file).
.RE
.
.\" ─── resolve ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
.SS h5i resolve \fIOURS\fR \fITHEIRS\fR \fIFILE\fR
Resolve a branch conflict using CRDT-based semantic merging.
Reconstructs the conflict-free state from Git Notes; no interactive
merge editor required.
.PP
.B Arguments
.RS 4
.TP
.I OURS
OID of the local branch.
.TP
.I THEIRS
OID of the incoming branch.
.TP
.I FILE
Relative path to the file to resolve.
.RE
.
.\" ─── rollback ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
.SS h5i rollback \fIINTENT\fR [\fIOPTIONS\fR]
Revert the commit whose stored prompt or message best matches the
natural-language
.I INTENT
description.
Uses semantic search via Claude when
.B ANTHROPIC_API_KEY
is set; falls back to keyword matching otherwise.
.PP
Before reverting, h5i checks whether any later commits declared the
matched commit as a
.B \-\-caused\-by
dependency and warns accordingly.
.PP
.B Options
.RS 4
.TP
.BI \-l,\ \-\-limit\  N
Number of recent commits to search (default:
.BR 50 ).
.TP
.B \-\-dry\-run
Show the matched commit without reverting.
.TP
.B \-y,\ \-\-yes
Skip the confirmation prompt (useful in CI).
.RE
.
.\" ─── session ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
.SS h5i session \-\-file \fIFILE\fR
Start a real-time recording session for
.IR FILE .
Detects changes via the
.B notify
crate and syncs them into a per-file Yrs CRDT document stored in
.IR .git/.h5i/crdt/ .
Press
.B Ctrl+C
to stop.
.
.\" ─── serve ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
.SS h5i serve [\fIOPTIONS\fR]
Launch the embedded web dashboard.
.PP
.B Options
.RS 4
.TP
.BI \-p,\ \-\-port\  PORT
Port to listen on (default:
.BR 7150 ).
.RE
.PP
Dashboard tabs:
.RS 4
.IP \(bu 2
.B Timeline
\(em full commit history with test-status borders, AI prompt panels,
and per-commit Audit buttons
.IP \(bu 2
.B Summary
\(em aggregate stats, agent leaderboard, filter pills
.IP \(bu 2
.B Integrity
\(em audit any commit message + prompt against all twelve rules without committing
.IP \(bu 2
.B Intent Graph
\(em directed graph of causal commit chains
.IP \(bu 2
.B Memory
\(em browse and diff Claude memory snapshots
.IP \(bu 2
.B Sessions
\(em exploration footprint, uncertainty heatmap, and churn for each commit
.RE
.
.\" ─── push ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
.SS h5i push [\fIOPTIONS\fR]
Push all h5i refs
.RI ( refs/h5i/notes
and
.IR refs/h5i/memory )
to a remote in one shot.
.PP
.B Options
.RS 4
.TP
.BI \-r,\ \-\-remote\  REMOTE
Remote to push to (default:
.BR origin ).
.RE
.
.\" ─── hooks ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
.SS h5i hooks
Print the Claude Code hook configuration required for automatic prompt
capture.
Outputs the shell script to save as
.I ~/.claude/hooks/h5i\-capture\-prompt.sh
and the
.I ~/.claude/settings.json
snippet to register it.
After setup, every Claude Code conversation automatically writes the
prompt to
.I .git/.h5i/pending_context.json
where it is consumed and cleared by the next
.BR "h5i commit" .
.
.\" ─── resume ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
.SS h5i resume [\fIBRANCH\fR]
Generate a structured session-handoff briefing assembled entirely from
local h5i data (no AI API call required).
Shows: branch / HEAD commit, project goal and milestone progress
(from
.IR .h5i\-ctx/ ),
last session statistics, high-risk files (weighted by uncertainty +
churn), causal exposure, memory changes since the last snapshot, and
a suggested opening prompt.
.PP
.B Risk score formula
.RS 4
.PP
.B risk\ =\ 0.4\ \(mu\ (1\ \-\ avg_confidence)\ +\ 0.3\ \(mu\ churn_score\ +\ 0.3\ \(mu\ (signal_count\ /\ max_signal_count)
.PP
Files are ranked descending and the top five are shown.
.RE
.
.\" ─── memory ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
.SS h5i memory \fIACTION\fR
Version-control Claude Code's persistent memory files alongside your code.
Claude Code stores per-project memory in
.IR "~/.claude/projects/<repo\-path>/memory/" .
h5i snapshots these files into
.I .git/.h5i/memory/<commit\-oid>/
and exposes them through the
.I refs/h5i/memory
ref.
.PP
.B Actions
.RS 4
.TP
.B snapshot
Snapshot current memory into the sidecar.
.RS 4
.TP
.BI \-\-commit\  OID
Associate with this commit OID (default: HEAD).
.TP
.BI \-\-path\  DIR
Override the source directory (default:
.IR "~/.claude/projects/<repo>/memory/" ).
.RE
.TP
.B log
List all memory snapshots.
.TP
.B diff [\fIFROM\fR [\fITO\fR]]
Show how memory changed between two snapshots.
Omit
.I TO
to compare against live memory.
Omit both to compare the two most recent snapshots.
.TP
.B restore \fICOMMIT\fR [\fB\-y\fR]
Restore Claude's memory to the state captured at
.IR COMMIT .
Prompts for confirmation unless
.B \-y
is given.
.TP
.B push [\fB\-r\fR \fIREMOTE\fR]
Push snapshots to a remote via
.IR refs/h5i/memory .
.TP
.B pull [\fB\-r\fR \fIREMOTE\fR]
Pull snapshots from a remote.
.RE
.
.\" ─── notes ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
.SS h5i notes \fIACTION\fR
Parse Claude Code session logs and attach enriched metadata
(exploration footprint, uncertainty heatmap, omission report, file churn,
intent graph) to commits.
Analyses are stored in
.IR .git/.h5i/session_log/<commit\-oid>/analysis.json .
.PP
.B Actions
.RS 4
.TP
.B analyze [\-\-session \fIJSONL\fR] [\-\-commit \fIOID\fR]
Parse a session log and link it to a commit (default: HEAD).
Auto-detects the latest Claude Code session log when
.B \-\-session
is omitted.
.TP
.B show [\fICOMMIT\fR]
Show stored session analysis for
.I COMMIT
(default: HEAD).
Displays files consulted vs edited and the causal chain summary.
.TP
.B footprint [\fIOID\fR]
Exploration footprint: every file the AI read before making a change,
revealing implicit dependencies that Git's diff does not capture.
.TP
.B uncertainty [\-\-commit \fIOID\fR] [\-\-file \fIPATH\fR]
Uncertainty heatmap.
Records moments where Claude expressed uncertainty: "not sure", "let me check", "this might break", etc.
Confidence thresholds:
.BR red\ (<35%) ,\  yellow\ (35\(en55%) ,\  green\ (>55%) .
.TP
.B omissions [\-\-commit \fIOID\fR] [\-\-file \fIPATH\fR]
Omission report.
Detects three categories of incomplete work left behind in Claude's
thinking blocks:
.RS 4
.TP
.B Deferral\ (red)
Claude acknowledged something and explicitly deferred it: "for now", "out of scope", "separate PR", "leave this for later".
.TP
.B Placeholder\ (yellow)
Claude inserted an admittedly incomplete implementation: "stub", "hardcoded for now", "simplified version", "workaround".
.TP
.B Unfulfilled promise\ (cyan)
Claude stated "I'll also update X" or "I should add Y" but the named file never appeared in the edit sequence.
.RE
.TP
.B churn [\-l \fIN\fR]
Per-file edit-churn scores across all analyzed sessions.
Churn = edits / (edits + reads).
Shows top
.I N
files (default: 20).
.TP
.B graph [\-l \fIN\fR] [\-\-mode \fIMODE\fR]
Visualize the chain of intents across recent commits.
.B \-\-mode prompt
(default) uses stored prompts;
.B \-\-mode analyze
calls Claude for richer intent extraction.
.TP
.B review [\-l \fIN\fR] [\-\-min\-score \fIF\fR] [\-\-json]
Identify commits most likely to need human review.
Scores are computed from uncertainty, churn, and signal density.
.B \-\-json
emits raw JSON instead of the styled table.
.RE
.
.\" ─── context ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
.SS h5i context \fIACTION\fR
Git-style branching and committing applied to agent
.I reasoning
rather than code.
Maintains a
.I .h5i\-ctx/
workspace based on arXiv:2508.00031.
.PP
.B Workspace layout
.RS 4
.nf
.I .h5i\-ctx/
    main.md                  \(em global roadmap: goal, milestones, notes
    branches/<branch>/
        commit.md            \(em milestone summaries (append-only)
        trace.md             \(em OTA execution trace
        metadata.yaml        \(em file structure, dependencies, env config
.fi
.RE
.PP
.B Actions
.RS 4
.TP
.B init \-\-goal \fITEXT\fR
Create the workspace with an initial project goal.
.TP
.B commit \fISUMMARY\fR [\-\-detail \fITEXT\fR]
Save a milestone checkpoint (one-line summary + optional detail).
.TP
.B branch \fINAME\fR [\-\-purpose \fITEXT\fR]
Create and switch to a new reasoning branch.
.TP
.B checkout \fINAME\fR
Switch to an existing reasoning branch.
.TP
.B merge \fIBRANCH\fR
Merge a completed branch's log and summaries into the current branch.
.TP
.B trace \-\-kind \fIKIND\fR \fICONTENT\fR
Append an OTA (Observe\(enThink\(enAct) trace entry.
Valid
.I KIND
values:
.BR OBSERVE ,\  THINK ,\  ACT ,\  NOTE
(case-insensitive).
.TP
.B show [\fIOPTIONS\fR]
Retrieve the current project state.
.RS 4
.TP
.BI \-\-branch\  NAME
Show a specific branch without switching.
.TP
.BI \-\-commit\  HASH
Show a specific commit entry by hash prefix.
.TP
.B \-\-trace
Include recent OTA trace lines.
.TP
.BI \-\-metadata\  SEGMENT
Pull a named section from
.IR metadata.yaml .
.TP
.BI \-\-window\  N
Number of recent commits to include (default: 3).
.TP
.BI \-\-trace\-offset\  N
Scroll back N lines from the end of the trace.
.RE
.TP
.B status
Quick overview: current branch, commit count, trace line count.
.TP
.B prompt
Print a Claude system prompt that explains how to use h5i context
commands inside an agent session.
.RE
.
.\" ─── vibe ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
.SS h5i vibe [\fIOPTIONS\fR]
Show an instant AI footprint audit of the repository: what fraction of
recent commits are AI-generated, which directories are fully AI-written,
and which files carry the highest risk.
.PP
Output is divided into five sections, printed only when non-empty:
.RS 4
.IP \(bu 2
.B AI %
\(em fraction of scanned commits that carry AI provenance metadata
.IP \(bu 2
.B Contributors
\(em count of distinct human authors and AI models, with names
.IP \(bu 2
.B Fully AI dirs
\(em directories where every commit is AI-generated (\(>= 2 commits)
.IP \(bu 2
.B Hot dirs
\(em directories with \(>= 80% AI commits (\(>= 3 commits)
.IP \(bu 2
.B Blind edits
\(em total blind edits from all analysed sessions and the file count
.IP \(bu 2
.B Risky files
\(em top 5 files with \(>= 70% AI commits plus at least one risk signal
.RE
.PP
A file is flagged when its AI commit ratio is \(>= 70% and at least one of:
no passing test metrics, one or more blind edits, or one or more
uncertainty annotations.
Blind-edit and uncertainty data come from session analyses stored by
.BR "h5i notes analyze" .
.PP
.B Options
.RS 4
.TP
.BI \-l,\ \-\-limit\  N
Number of recent commits to scan (default:
.BR 500 ).
.TP
.B \-\-json
Output raw JSON instead of the styled report.
.RE
.
.\" ─── mcp ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
.SS h5i mcp
Start the h5i MCP (Model Context Protocol) server on stdio.
Implements the
.B 2024-11-05
specification over a newline-delimited JSON-RPC\~2.0 transport.
.PP
Register with Claude Code by adding to
.I ~/.claude/settings.json
or
.IR .claude/settings.json :
.PP
.RS 4
.nf
{
  "mcpServers": {
    "h5i": { "command": "h5i", "args": ["mcp"] }
  }
}
.fi
.RE
.PP
.B Capabilities
.RS 4
.TP
.B tools
Fifteen tools covering
.BR h5i_log ,\  h5i_blame ,\  h5i_notes_* ,
and
.B h5i_context_*
(see
.IR MANUAL.md ).
.TP
.B resources
Two resources:
.B h5i://context/current
(live reasoning workspace state) and
.B h5i://log/recent
(10 most recent commits with AI provenance).
.TP
.B resources.subscribe
Both resources support live push notifications.
.RE
.PP
.B Resource subscriptions
.RS 4
.PP
The server advertises
.B capabilities.resources.subscribe\ =\ true
in the
.B initialize
response.
Send
.B resources/subscribe
with a
.I uri
parameter to register; the server spawns a 2-second polling thread per URI
and pushes
.B notifications/resources/updated
whenever the content changes.
Send
.B resources/unsubscribe
to stop.
.PP
Subscribable URIs:
.B h5i://log/recent
(fires when a new
.B h5i commit
lands) and
.B h5i://context/current
(fires when the context workspace is updated).
.RE
.
.\" ─── policy ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
.SS h5i policy \fISUBCOMMAND\fR
Manage governance rules for AI-assisted commits.
Rules live in
.I .h5i/policy.toml
(workdir, not inside
.IR .git/ ;
commit it alongside your code).
Policy is evaluated automatically on every
.B h5i commit\c
; violations block the commit unless
.B \-\-force
is passed.
.PP
.B Subcommands
.RS 4
.TP
.B init
Create
.I .h5i/policy.toml
with a commented-out starter configuration.
.TP
.B check
Dry-run policy check against the currently staged files without committing.
Exit code is non-zero when at least one error-level violation is found.
.TP
.B show
Print the parsed policy configuration.
.RE
.PP
.B Policy file schema
.RS 4
.nf
[commit]
require_ai_provenance = true   # reject commits with no AI provenance
min_message_len = 10           # reject short messages
require_audit_on_flagged_paths = true
label = "company-standard-v1"

[paths."src/auth/**"]
require_ai_provenance = true   # enforced at commit time
require_audit = true           # enforced at commit time (needs flag above)
max_ai_ratio = 0.8             # compliance-only: flag if >80% AI commits
max_blind_edit_ratio = 0.3     # compliance-only: flag if >30% blind edits
.fi
.RE
.PP
Glob patterns support
.BR * ,\  ** ,
and
.BR ? .
.
.\" ─── compliance ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
.SS h5i compliance [\fIOPTIONS\fR]
Generate a compliance audit report over a date range.
Walks the commit history, re-evaluates policy rules, and aggregates session
data (blind edits, uncertainty signals) into a text, JSON, or HTML report.
.PP
.B Options
.RS 4
.TP
.BI \-\-since " YYYY-MM-DD"
Start of date range (inclusive).
.TP
.BI \-\-until " YYYY-MM-DD"
End of date range (inclusive).
.TP
.BI \-\-format " fmt"
Output format:
.BR text " (default), " json ", or " html .
The HTML output is a self-contained dark-theme page.
.TP
.BI \-\-output " FILE"
Write the report to a file instead of stdout.
.TP
.BI \-l, \-\-limit " N"
Maximum commits to scan (default: 500).
.RE
.PP
.B What is checked
.RS 4
.TP
At commit time:
.BR commit.require_ai_provenance ,\  commit.min_message_len ,\  paths.*.require_ai_provenance ,
and
.B paths.*.require_audit
(the last two require the global
.B require_audit_on_flagged_paths
flag).
.TP
Compliance-only:
.B paths.*.max_ai_ratio
and
.B paths.*.max_blind_edit_ratio
\(em trend rules designed for historical analysis rather than blocking
individual commits.
.RE
.PP
.B Example
.RS 4
.nf
h5i compliance \-\-since 2025-01-01 \-\-format html \-\-output report.html
.fi
.RE
.
.SH INTEGRITY RULES
The
.B \-\-audit
flag runs twelve deterministic, pure string/stat checks against the diff.
No AI and no network access are required.
.PP
.TP
.BR CREDENTIAL_LEAK \ (Violation)
Added line contains a credential keyword + assignment + quoted value, or a PEM header.
.TP
.BR CODE_EXECUTION \ (Violation)
Added non-comment line contains
.BR eval() ,\  exec() ,\  os.system() ,
or
.BR subprocess.* .
.TP
.BR CI_CD_MODIFIED \ (Violation)
.IR .github/workflows/ ,
Jenkinsfile, etc. modified without CI/CD intent in the prompt.
.TP
.BR SENSITIVE_FILE_MODIFIED \ (Warning)
.IR .env ,\  .pem ,\  .key ,\  id_rsa ,\  credentials
appear in the diff.
.TP
.BR LOCKFILE_MODIFIED \ (Warning)
.IR Cargo.lock ,\  package\-lock.json ,\  go.sum
changed without dependency intent stated.
.TP
.BR UNDECLARED_DELETION \ (Warning)
More than 60% of changes are deletions with no deletion/refactor intent.
.TP
.BR SCOPE_EXPANSION \ (Warning)
Prompt names a specific file but other source files were also modified.
.TP
.BR LARGE_DIFF \ (Warning)
More than 500 total lines changed.
.TP
.BR REFACTOR_ANOMALY \ (Warning)
.RI \[dq] refactor \[dq]
intent but insertions are 3x or more the deletions.
.TP
.BR PERMISSION_CHANGE \ (Warning)
.BR chmod\ 777 ,\  sudo ,\  setuid ,\  chown\ root
in added lines.
.TP
.BR BINARY_FILE_CHANGED \ (Info)
A binary file appears in the diff.
.TP
.BR CONFIG_FILE_MODIFIED \ (Info)
.IR .yaml ,\  .toml ,\  .json ,\  .ini ,
etc. modified.
.
.SH TEST RESULTS SCHEMA
Pass a JSON file to
.B \-\-test\-results
matching this schema (all fields optional):
.PP
.nf
{
  "tool":          "jest",
  "passed":        42,
  "failed":        1,
  "skipped":       3,
  "total":         46,
  "duration_secs": 4.7,
  "coverage":      0.87,
  "exit_code":     1,
  "summary":       "42 passed, 1 failed in 4.70s"
}
.fi
.PP
.B exit_code
takes precedence over counts when determining pass/fail.
.B total
is computed from counts if omitted.
Two bundled adapters are provided:
.TP
.I script/h5i\-pytest\-adapter.py
Runs pytest, uses
.B pytest\-json\-report
when available, falls back to output parsing.
.TP
.I script/h5i\-cargo\-test\-adapter.sh
Runs
.BR "cargo test" ,
accumulates counts across lib, integration, and doc-test sections.
.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B H5I_PROMPT
Default prompt for
.BR "h5i commit" .
.TP
.B H5I_MODEL
Default model name for
.BR "h5i commit" .
.TP
.B H5I_AGENT_ID
Default agent ID for
.BR "h5i commit" .
.TP
.B H5I_TEST_RESULTS
Default path to a test results JSON file.
.TP
.B ANTHROPIC_API_KEY
When set, enables semantic search in
.B h5i rollback
and Claude-assisted intent extraction in
.BR "h5i notes graph \-\-mode analyze" .
.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I .git/.h5i/
Sidecar root; all persistent metadata.
.TP
.I .git/.h5i/ast/
SHA-256-keyed S-expression AST snapshots.
.TP
.I .git/.h5i/crdt/
Yjs CRDT document state.
.TP
.I .git/.h5i/delta/
Append-only CRDT update logs, one file per source path (keyed by sha256(path)).
Format: [length: u32][update bytes].
.TP
.I .git/.h5i/memory/<commit-oid>/
Claude memory snapshots.
Each directory contains memory files plus
.I _meta.json
(snapshot timestamp and file count).
.TP
.I .git/.h5i/session_log/<commit-oid>/analysis.json
Structured session log analysis produced by
.BR "h5i notes analyze" .
.TP
.I .git/.h5i/pending_context.json
Transient file written by the Claude Code hook; consumed and deleted
at the next
.BR "h5i commit" .
.TP
.I .h5i-ctx/
Context workspace (created by
.BR "h5i context init" ).
.TP
.I refs/h5i/notes
Git ref storing AI provenance, test metrics, causal links, and integrity
reports as JSON blobs attached to each commit.
Inspect with:
.B git notes \-\-ref refs/h5i/notes show <oid>
.TP
.I refs/h5i/memory
Git ref storing Claude memory snapshots as a linear commit history of
git tree objects.
.TP
.I ~/.claude/projects/<repo>/memory/
Claude Code's default per-project memory directory (source for snapshots).
.TP
.I ~/.claude/hooks/h5i-capture-prompt.sh
Hook script printed by
.BR "h5i hooks" .
.
.SH STORAGE
Neither
.I refs/h5i/notes
nor
.I refs/h5i/memory
is included in a plain
.BR "git push" " / " "git pull" .
Share them with:
.PP
.RS 4
.nf
h5i push                             # push both refs to origin
git push origin refs/h5i/notes
git push origin refs/h5i/memory
.fi
.RE
.PP
Add fetch refspecs to
.I .git/config
so
.B git pull
picks them up automatically:
.PP
.RS 4
.nf
[remote "origin"]
    fetch = +refs/h5i/notes:refs/h5i/notes
    fetch = +refs/h5i/memory:refs/h5i/memory
.fi
.RE
.
.SH EXAMPLES
.SS Basic AI commit
.nf
h5i init
git add src/auth.rs
h5i commit \-m "add rate limiting" \\
    \-\-prompt "add per-IP rate limiting to the auth endpoint" \\
    \-\-model claude\-sonnet\-4\-6 \\
    \-\-agent claude\-code \\
    \-\-audit \-\-tests
.fi
.SS Causal chain
.nf
h5i commit \-m "fix off-by-one in validate_token" \\
    \-\-caused\-by a3f9c2b \\
    \-\-prompt "fix the bug introduced by the rate limiter"
.fi
.SS Intent-based rollback
.nf
h5i rollback "the OAuth login changes" \-\-dry\-run
h5i rollback "rate limiting" \-\-yes
.fi
.SS Session analysis workflow
.nf
# End of session
h5i notes analyze
h5i memory snapshot
h5i push

# Start of next session
h5i resume
h5i notes show
h5i notes uncertainty \-\-file src/auth.rs
h5i notes omissions
.fi
.SS Context workspace
.nf
h5i context init \-\-goal "build OAuth2 login system"
h5i context trace \-\-kind OBSERVE "HttpClient::send has no retry logic"
h5i context trace \-\-kind THINK   "exponential backoff with jitter is safest"
h5i context trace \-\-kind ACT     "added retry loop in send() with 5-attempt cap"
h5i context commit "implemented retry loop" \\
    \-\-detail "capped at 5 attempts; uses tokio::time::sleep"
h5i context branch experiment/sync\-retry \-\-purpose "try sync fallback"
# ...explore...
h5i context checkout main
h5i context status
.fi
.SS Team workflow
.nf
# Alice
h5i commit \-m "add rate limiting" \-\-prompt "..." \-\-agent claude\-code
h5i memory snapshot
h5i push
git push origin main

# Bob
git pull
h5i log
h5i memory pull
h5i memory restore <alice\-commit>
.fi
.
